306
00:13:31,880 --> 00:13:33,720
Okay, okay, I lied—
I like her.

307
00:13:33,790 --> 00:13:35,130
Oh, really?

308
00:13:35,190 --> 00:13:38,430
Yeah. Woof.

309
00:13:38,490 --> 00:13:39,790
There you go.

310
00:13:39,860 --> 00:13:41,970
Wait, don't open the door.

311
00:13:42,030 --> 00:13:43,670
Why not?
(doorbell ringing)

312
00:13:43,730 --> 00:13:44,890
Coming.

313
00:13:44,960 --> 00:13:46,790
Go to your room.

314
00:13:46,870 --> 00:13:47,870
What are you nuts?

315
00:13:47,930 --> 00:13:49,700
Please don't hit on her.

316
00:13:49,770 --> 00:13:50,640
Hit on who?

317
00:13:50,700 --> 00:13:51,830
Taylor's mom.

318
00:13:51,900 --> 00:13:53,700
Why would I hit
on Taylor's mom?

319
00:13:53,770 --> 00:13:55,070
Well, because
she's kind of pretty,

320
00:13:55,140 --> 00:13:57,940
and you'll hit on
anything with a pulse.

321
00:13:58,010 --> 00:13:59,940
Where'd you get that?

322
00:14:00,010 --> 00:14:01,010
My mom.

323
00:14:01,080 --> 00:14:02,110
Oh, well...

324
00:14:02,180 --> 00:14:04,780
And my dad, Berta,
Rose, Grandma...

325
00:14:04,850 --> 00:14:05,950
Okay, okay.

326
00:14:06,020 --> 00:14:07,690
The UPS man...

327
00:14:07,750 --> 00:14:09,420
All right.

328
00:14:09,490 --> 00:14:10,630
And when you hit on
people I know,

329
00:14:10,690 --> 00:14:11,850
everything gets screwed up

330
00:14:11,920 --> 00:14:13,690
where I have to find
a new guitar teacher,

331
00:14:13,760 --> 00:14:15,190
a new karate class,
Cub Scout troop...

332
00:14:15,260 --> 00:14:16,660
Okay, okay, I get it.

333
00:14:16,730 --> 00:14:17,800
godmother.

334
00:14:17,860 --> 00:14:20,060
You don't have
to worry.

335
00:14:20,130 --> 00:14:22,730
I'm not going to risk
our friendship over
"kind of pretty."

336
00:14:22,800 --> 00:14:23,900
So you won't
hit on her?

337
00:14:23,970 --> 00:14:25,730
Absolutely not.

338
00:14:27,810 --> 00:14:30,620
Hi. I'm Taylor's mom.

339
00:14:32,280 --> 00:14:33,080
Scratch that.

340
00:14:39,850 --> 00:14:41,580
Great. Bye.

341
00:14:48,530 --> 00:14:49,870
You promised.

342
00:14:49,930 --> 00:14:52,900
No, no. No, no. The head
that made the promise

343
00:14:52,970 --> 00:14:54,870
is not the one that broke it.

344
00:14:57,570 --> 00:15:00,540
And besides, you said she
was just kind of pretty?

345
00:15:00,610 --> 00:15:01,710
Who do you
consider hot?

346
00:15:01,770 --> 00:15:03,270
Taylor.

347
00:15:03,340 --> 00:15:04,810
Taylor's 12.

348
00:15:04,880 --> 00:15:06,920
Hello?

349
00:15:06,980 --> 00:15:09,250
Come on, what's the worst thing
that could happen

350
00:15:09,320 --> 00:15:11,460
if I go out with your
little friend's mom?

351
00:15:11,520 --> 00:15:13,320
Do I have to explain
it to you again?

352
00:15:13,390 --> 00:15:15,160
My guitar teacher,
my karate coach...

353
00:15:15,220 --> 00:15:16,480
Okay, okay.

354
00:15:16,560 --> 00:15:19,700
I can't show my face
at the comic book store.

355
00:15:19,760 --> 00:15:22,770
All right, but the worst thing
doesn't have to happen.

356
00:15:22,830 --> 00:15:25,740
Would you please just
not go out with her?

357
00:15:25,800 --> 00:15:29,210
Tell you what—
I'll make you a deal.

358
00:15:29,270 --> 00:15:30,710
I'll give up Taylor's mom
in exchange

359
00:15:30,770 --> 00:15:33,500
for you washing my car
once a week for the next month.

360
00:15:33,570 --> 00:15:34,840
Done.

361
00:15:34,910 --> 00:15:36,410
That includes Turtle Wax,
tire dressing

362
00:15:36,480 --> 00:15:38,350
and vacuuming the carpets.
Oh, man.

363
00:15:38,410 --> 00:15:39,870
Hey, hey, hey, hey, the woman
is recently divorced.

364
00:15:39,950 --> 00:15:41,690
I didn't ask for her number,
she gave it to me.

365
00:15:41,750 --> 00:15:43,660
Do you know what that means?
No.

366
00:15:43,720 --> 00:15:46,790
That means one, maybe two
dinners, and...

367
00:15:48,350 --> 00:15:50,490
You're waxing my car.

368
00:15:50,560 --> 00:15:53,300
All right.

369
00:15:53,360 --> 00:15:56,730
You're lucky you're not
painting the house.

370
00:15:56,800 --> 00:15:59,770
The sacrifices we make
for our kids.

371
00:15:59,830 --> 00:16:01,730
Hey.

372
00:16:01,800 --> 00:16:03,870
Hey.

373
00:16:03,940 --> 00:16:05,340
You look like crap.

374
00:16:05,400 --> 00:16:07,700
Thank you.
You look terrific.

375
00:16:07,770 --> 00:16:09,500
I feel terrific.

376
00:16:09,580 --> 00:16:10,920
The key is a good night's sleep.

377
00:16:10,980 --> 00:16:12,750
Yeah, listen, uh,

378
00:16:12,810 --> 00:16:14,510
I have to talk to you.

379
00:16:14,580 --> 00:16:16,740
This is a bad
time, Alan.
How come?

380
00:16:16,820 --> 00:16:18,360
Because you want
to talk to me.

381
00:16:19,820 --> 00:16:20,990
Okay, what?

382
00:16:21,050 --> 00:16:23,520
Uh, you know I love you, right?

383
00:16:23,590 --> 00:16:26,690
Alan, are you
breaking up with me?

384
00:16:26,760 --> 00:16:29,530
Would you just shut up
and listen to me?

385
00:16:29,600 --> 00:16:31,400
Pick one, Alan.

386
00:16:31,460 --> 00:16:35,530
All right, all right,
I talked to a therapist.

387
00:16:35,600 --> 00:16:39,770
And I think
I learned something.

388
00:16:39,840 --> 00:16:42,410
Nah, too easy.
Go ahead.

389
00:16:42,480 --> 00:16:44,650
The thing is...

390
00:16:44,710 --> 00:16:47,740
all these years of watching
your life go so smoothly,

391
00:16:47,810 --> 00:16:49,510
while I stumble back and forth

392
00:16:49,580 --> 00:16:51,980
between humiliation
and abject failure,

393
00:16:52,050 --> 00:16:54,780
has resulted in me harboring
a lot of anger

394
00:16:54,850 --> 00:16:56,280
and jealousy towards you.

395
00:16:56,360 --> 00:16:57,660
Yeah, I get that.

396
00:16:57,720 --> 00:17:00,420
How could it not?

397
00:17:00,490 --> 00:17:04,790
Anyway, I think the tension
between my love for you

398
00:17:04,860 --> 00:17:07,600
and my resentment of you
is what's causing my insomnia.

399
00:17:07,670 --> 00:17:09,540
And?

400
00:17:09,600 --> 00:17:11,770
And I thought maybe if
I got it out in the open,

401
00:17:11,840 --> 00:17:12,840
it might help me sleep.

402
00:17:12,910 --> 00:17:14,710
So how do you feel now?

403
00:17:14,770 --> 00:17:16,840
Better, actually.

404
00:17:16,910 --> 00:17:18,920
Like... like a weight
has been lifted.

405
00:17:18,980 --> 00:17:20,520
Well, good.

406
00:17:20,580 --> 00:17:21,780
Yeah, maybe that's it.

407
00:17:21,850 --> 00:17:23,620
Maybe all I needed to do
was unload.

408
00:17:23,680 --> 00:17:27,750
Well, a good unloading
usually makes me drowsy.

409
00:17:27,820 --> 00:17:28,920
You're disgusting.

410
00:17:28,990 --> 00:17:30,330
True...

411
00:17:30,390 --> 00:17:33,300
